Based on the visible screen, you can browse the image results by scrolling down or selecting an image. To perform the task of browsing images as per the plan, you may scroll to view more images.

Here is the action to scroll down:
```json
[
    {"action_type":"MouseAction","mouse_action_type":"scroll_down","scroll_repeat":3}
]
```

If you want to select an image, move the cursor to the chosen image and click. For example, to click on the first image in the second row, which is approximately at the center of the width of the screen (512) and a bit down from the top (around 250 pixels down), the action would be:

```json
[
    {"action_type":"MouseAction","mouse_action_type":"click","mouse_button":"left","mouse_position":{"width":512,"height":250}}
]
```
